As @widedays would have taken place tomorrow, they are going ahead with hosting free virtual sessions, chats and hangouts. Reserve your place for tomorrow's sessions:

Tune in to #PRSPresentsLCKDWN tomorrow to help support the music industry. Hosted in aid of the PRS Emergency Relief Fund, this virtual event pays tribute to the songwriters and composers getting us through this difficult time.

If you are a musician seeking support and advice during this crucial time, make sure to visit @HelpMusicians' http://coronamusicians.info, as the website is updated regularly with resources to support your mental health and creative development.

Did you know? The PPL Momentum Music Fund with @prsfoundation has four deadlines a year, with the next upcoming deadline being 25 May. Artists/bands applying for the PPL Momentum Music Fund must be at a crucial tipping point in their careers. Read more: https://www.ppluk.com/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-ppl-momentum-music-fund/
From 2 - 3 pm today, you can experience a behind the scenes home studio tour with music presenter @mrstevelevine and @BBC6Music presenter @ChrisHawkinsUK. Register for your spot below.

Deadline approaching: @ISM_music's wants to know how the Coronavirus Business Interruption Loan Scheme (CBILS) is supporting the music sector. If you've applied for the scheme, take their survey before 22 April to help them inform Government of any needed improvements.

Last week we launched the Most Played Tracks of the Decade (2010 - 2019) chart via @BBCRadio2. You can re-listen to the show, as @scott_mills counts down the top 40 songs that were most played on UK radio and television since 2010.

We are providing further funding to @HelpMusiciansUK Hardship Fund as part of the £1.5m donation coordinated by @bpi_music. Together with @amazonmusic, @BRITs and major & independent record labels, we will be able to support 2,500 more musicians https://bit.ly/3etfurN

The @bpi_music annual yearbook All About the Music 2020 gives a detailed insight into the year in UK recorded music in 2019 through lots of facts, figures and informed analysis. Read more here: https://bpi.co.uk/news-analysis/bpi-publishes-all-about-the-music-2020/

Over the weekend, @GlblCtzn launched a live concert, One World: #TogetherAtHome, to support @WHO's COVID-19 Solidarity Respond Fund. If you missed it, you can re-live the music and watch the incredible performances at the following link:

We want to hear from you! Help @UK_Music and its member organisations to be more effective in speaking to the government on issues that impact music creators. Fill out the Creator's Survey and help contribute to the #MusicByNumbers report: https://www.surveymonkey.co.uk/r/PPL2020CS

We are proud to be pledging £700,000 to three music industry hardship funds as we continue to support music creators during this time. We are donating to the @HelpMusiciansUK Hardship Fund, @WeAreTheMUHardship Fund & the @AIM_UK Support Fund. Learn more: https://www.ppluk.com/ppl-pledges-700000-to-music-industry-hardship-funds/

Coronavirus Advice: The music industry’s representative body, @UK_Music has brought together a directory of advice from the Government, as well as different music trade bodies. Learn more here: https://www.ppluk.com/membership/coronavirus-advice/
